{"source_key":"sha256-784c2f10bfe4a26d66c37ad545f72f01","record_index":14616,"record_hash":"sha256:8469cf150aaf6ebc3909eff354ce7df2f8128691dec3ed5bad3d31ae654382f9","timestamp":"2026-05-09T17:59:07.798Z","kind":"tool_result","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:function_call_output","role":null,"text":"Chunk ID: b9a90a\nWall time: 0.0000 seconds\nProcess exited with code 0\nOriginal token count: 1089\nOutput:\n\n```text\nsha256(agent + NUL + canonical-transcript-path-bytes)\n```\n\n`source-key` identifies the captured source file and is derived from the agent\nplus canonical transcript path bytes.\n\n## Transcript Envelope\n\nKeep one ordered `:transcript` list per durable GitButler session. Each list item\nis one redacted JSON envelope with only per-record data:\n\n```json\n{\n\t\"schema\": \"gitbutler.agent-transcript.v1\",\n\t\"source_key\": \"sha256-...\",\n\t\"record_index\": 0,\n\t\"record_hash\": \"sha256:...\",\n\t\"timestamp\": \"2026-05-07T09:08:43.427Z\",\n\t\"event_kind\": \"response_item\",\n\t\"event_category\": \"message\",\n\t\"role\": \"assistant\",\n\t\"content_text\": \"redacted normalized text when easy to extract\",\n\t\"tool_name\": null,\n\t\"source_record\": {}\n}\n```\n\nSlim normalized fields support timeline browsing and handoff without reparsing\nevery provider-specific record:\n\n- `event_category`: `session`, `context`, `message`, `tool`, or `other`\n- `role` and `content_text`: conversation body when extraction is obvious\n- `tool_name`: obvious tool activity\n- `source_record`: redacted provider record for provenance and future adapters\n\nOmit repeated session/source metadata from each envelope. Also omit cwd, git\nbranch, provider session ids, message ids, parent ids, turn ids, and redaction\ncounters from top-level envelope fields.\n\nRecord hashes and dedupe use the original trimmed JSONL bytes, not the redacted\nenvelope.\n\n## Deduplication\n\nUse stable record hashes:\n\n```text\nsha256(trimmed raw JSONL line bytes)\n```\n\nThe session-level `record-hashes` set tracks metadata dedupe. Transcript append\ndedupe is rebuilt from the stored envelope list by reading each envelope's\n`record_hash`. This keeps transcript backfill possible if the list is missing\nwhile the record hash set still exists.\n\n## Future Association Model\n\nDo not attach transcript data directly to branches, commits, changes, or pull\nrequests in the POC. The project session is the durable object.\n\nLater, w\n[TRUNCATED]\nuire a later privacy and product\ndecision.\n\nThe transcript parser should not write GitMeta. The GitMeta writer should not\nknow provider-specific transcript shapes beyond the normalized record it\nreceives.\n\n## Target And Associations\n\nThe durable session object should stay on the `project` target by default. Even\nwhen future code can identify a branch, change, commit, or pull request, those\nobjects should reference project session keys rather than own transcript data.\n\nThat keeps session handoff possible before code exists and avoids bad ownership\nguesses when one agent session contributes to multiple GitButler branches.\n\nFuture relationship keys can look like:\n\n```text\n<branch/change/commit target>\n  gitbutler:agent-sessions = set<session-key>\n```\n\n## GitMeta Writer\n\nThe writer is the only code that should depend directly on `git-meta-lib`.\n\nResponsibilities:\n\n- open `git_meta_lib::Session`\n- resolve a `git_meta_lib::Target`\n- maintain `gitbutler:agent-sessions = set<session-key>`\n- write session keys under `gitbutler:agent-session:<session-key>:*`\n- append redacted transcript envelopes\n- keep metadata hashes and transcript envelope hashes separate enough for\n  idempotent repeated capture and transcript backfill\n\nThe writer should return a report and never print.\n\n## Privacy Boundary\n\nCapture writes shareable-ready keys but does not publish them. Serialization,\npush, fetch, and sync require a later privacy/product decision.\n\nAll stored agentlog values copied from transcripts are redacted before writing.\nThe POC does not store raw provider session ids.\n\n## Future Associations\n\nDo not implement branch, PR, change, or commit associations in this POC. Later,\nwhen GitButler has an explicit target, write relationship references like:\n\n```text\n<branch/change/commit target>\n  gitbutler:agent-sessions = set<session-key>\n```\n\nThe durable session remains project-scoped. See\n[Future Use Cases](future-use-cases.md).\n\n## Acceptance Tests\n\nMinimum tests before calling the POC done:\n\n- `cargo test -p but-agentlog` passes.\n","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-09T17:59:07.798Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}